This press gaggle by Principal Deputy Press Secretary Josh Earnest took place aboard Air Force One en route to Martha's Vineyard, Massachusetts. Earnest responded to questions regarding various topics, including whether President Obama planned to call Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu, the U.S. concern about the security situation in Sinai, how the President would monitor the volatility in the markets during his vacation, the White House's reaction to market swings and warnings of a potential recession, the timing of the President's jobs speech, the President's vacation plans and activities, the dollar value of the Syria sanctions, and the diplomatic efforts to isolate the Assad regime. Earnest also mentioned that the President would be receiving regular updates from his economic team and his counterterrorism advisor during his time in Martha's Vineyard.